---

## ğŸ—£ How to explain this in interview (exact words)

> Developer pushes code to AWS CodeCommit.
> CodePipeline triggers CodeBuild to build and test the application.
> If the build is successful, CodeDeploy deploys the application to EC2 or ECS.
> CloudWatch is used to monitor logs and performance.

---

## ğŸ” Role of each AWS service (1-line each)

* **CodeCommit** â†’ Source code repository
* **CodeBuild** â†’ Build and run tests
* **CodePipeline** â†’ Manages CI/CD workflow
* **CodeDeploy** â†’ Deploys application
* **CloudWatch** â†’ Monitoring and logs

---

## â­ One-line interview gold

> AWS CI/CD uses CodePipeline to automate build, test, and deployment using CodeCommit, CodeBuild, and CodeDeploy.

